doc.after: The ICAO airline designator is a code assigned by the International Civil Aviation Organization ICAO to aircraft operating agencies aeronautical authorities and services related to international aviation each of whom is allocated both a three letter designator and a telephony designator These codes are unique by airline unlike the IATA airline designator codes see section above The designators are listed in ICAO Document 8585 Designators for Aircraft Operating Agencies Aeronautical Authorities and Services
